Atlantis

Atlantis is a British fantasy-adventure television programme, inspired by Greek mythology and created and executive produced by Johnny Capps (Merlin and Sugar Rush), Julian Murphy (Merlin and Sugar Rush) and Howard Overman (Misfits and Vexed), which first aired in the UK on 28 September 2013.

The city of Atlantis is a strange, ancient dwelling; a world of bull leaping, of snake-haired goddesses and of palaces so vast it was said they were built by giants. Young Jason arrives in the city and an epic adventure begins.
